{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Rom|10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","chapter":10,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":1,"text":"Brothers and sisters, my heart’s desire and prayer to God concerning them is for their salvation.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":2,"text":"I can testify about them that they have zeal for God, but not according to knowledge.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":3,"text":"Since they are ignorant of the righteousness of God and attempted to establish their own righteousness, they have not submitted to God’s righteousness.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":4,"text":"For Christ is the end of the law for righteousness to everyone who believes,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":5,"text":"since Moses writes about the righteousness that is from the law: The one who does these things will live by them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":6,"text":"But the righteousness that comes from faith speaks like this: Do not say in your heart, “Who will go up to heaven?” that is, to bring Christ down","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":7,"text":"or, “Who will go down into the abyss?” that is, to bring Christ up from the dead.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":8,"text":"On the contrary, what does it say? The message is near you, in your mouth and in your heart. This is the message of faith that we proclaim:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":9,"text":"If you confess with your mouth, “Jesus is Lord,” and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":10,"text":"One believes with the heart, resulting in righteousness, and one confesses with the mouth, resulting in salvation.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":11,"text":"For the Scripture says, Everyone who believes on him will not be put to shame,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":12,"text":"since there is no distinction between Jew and Greek, because the same Lord of all richly blesses all who call on him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":13,"text":"For everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":14,"text":"How, then, can they call on him they have not believed in? And how can they believe without hearing about him? And how can they hear without a preacher?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":15,"text":"And how can they preach unless they are sent? As it is written: How beautiful are the feet of those who bring good news.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":16,"text":"But not all obeyed the gospel. For Isaiah says, Lord, who has believed our message?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":17,"text":"So faith comes from what is heard, and what is heard comes through the message about Christ.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":18,"text":"But I ask, “Did they not hear?” Yes, they did:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":19,"text":"But I ask, “Did Israel not understand?” First, Moses said,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":20,"text":"And Isaiah says boldly,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":10,"verse":21,"text":"But to Israel he says, All day long I have held out my hands to a disobedient and defiant people.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","chapter":10,"paragraphStarts":[1,14,19,20,21],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Righteousness by Faith Alone"},{"beforeVerse":14,"text":"Israel’s Rejection of the Message"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Brothers and sisters, my heart’s desire and prayer to God concerning them "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Other mss read God for Israel"},{"kind":"text","text":" is for their salvation. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Other mss read God for Israel"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I can testify about them that they have zeal for God, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 21:20","book":"Act","chapter":21,"verse":20,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" but not according to knowledge. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ac 21:20","book":"Act","chapter":21,"verse":20}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Since they are ignorant of the righteousness of God "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 1:17","book":"Rom","chapter":1,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and attempted to establish their own righteousness, they have not submitted to God’s righteousness. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 1:17","book":"Rom","chapter":1,"verse":17}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:10:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For Christ is the end "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Or goal"},{"kind":"text","text":" of the law for righteousness "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 7:1–4","book":"Rom","chapter":7,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 3:24","book":"Gal","chapter":3,"verse":24,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 4:5","book":"Gal","chapter":4,"verse":5,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" to everyone who believes, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 3:22","book":"Rom","chapter":3,"verse":22,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"c